        <lcIntro>
            <p>Topics stand on their own, but content in one topic often has relationships to other
                topics. A map file, for example, describes the sequence and hierarchy of topics for
                a deliverable.</p>
            <p>In addition to map files, we can create relationships among topics in several
                different ways:<ul id="ul_kfz_xtb_wr">
                    <li>conrefs</li>
                    <li>Cross-references</li>
                    <li>Related links</li>
                    <li>Relationship tables</li>
                </ul></p>
        </lcIntro>
